cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.DS 

This paper deals with the issue of node misbehavior in delay tolerant networks, which is a subfield of computer networking. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the need for making wireless technologies robust and resilient to attacks, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of simulation to measure network performance falls under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses the use of self-policing techniques, which can be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
